
			
									<h5>Release Date: 12 May 2021</h5>
				
									Neo4j 4.1.9 is a maintenance release with many important improvements and fixes.
<h3>Highlights</h3>

<ul>
   <li>Bump Netty to 4.1.63</li>
   <li>Fix an issue where creating or altering a user and setting their username and password to the same parameter would fail</li>
   <li>Admin commands stop using the ‘Xms’ heap setting</li>
   <li>Fix a bug where a transaction might be rolled back when performing multiple writes where the database catalog is changed concurrently.</li>
   <li>Fixes an issue with the length and size functions returning 1 instead of throwing an error for unsupported input values</li>
</ul>

<h3>Detailed Changes and Docs</h3>
For the complete list of all changes, please see <a href="https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j/wiki/Neo4j-4.1-changelog" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">the changelog</a>.
Look for 4.1 Operations manual <a href="https://neo4j.com/docs/operations-manual/4.1/">here</a>.				
					